Even with authentication, the endpoint returns **email addresses** in plaintext. Email addresses are PII under GDPR/CCPA and should only be returned when strictly necessary.

**Fix:** Return only what the consumer needs, and strip sensitive fields by default:

```js
app.get('/users', requireAuth, (req, res) => {
  const safeUsers = users.map(({ id, name }) => ({ id, name })); // drop email
